{
  "name": "Inner Sun",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/light.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You grant a creature that you have caused to glow brightly a weapon of light they may wield as a weapon. The weapon can be shaped into any melee weapon the holder is proficient with as a swift action, and initially appears as whatever weapon they choose. On a hit, this does an additional 1d4 fire damage + 1d4 damage for every 4 caster levels that you possess.</p>\n<p>The weapon can not harm invisible or translucent enemies or structures, and passes through them harmlessly, possibly damaging things on the other side. Targets that are reflective such as a mirror have a 50% miss chance against attacks with this weapon. If the creature deliberately lets go of the weapon, it disappears, but otherwise the creature can not be disarmed.</p>\n<p>You may target a weapon to grant it this additional fire damage, as if it were a weapon of light. This extra damage is subject to the same restrictions as a weapon of light (does not affect invisibile or translucent targets, 50% chance of not affecting reflective creatures).</p>\n",
